---
import ArticleLayout from '../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import PullQuote from '../components/ui/PullQuote.astro';
import RuleHeading from '../components/ui/RuleHeading.astro';
---

<ArticleLayout title="About">

  <header class="mb-10">
    <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-accent block mb-3">
      Profile
    </span>
    <h1 class="font-display font-black text-headline text-ink leading-[1.1] mb-3">
      Karan Gupta
    </h1>
    <p class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-muted">
      San Francisco, CA · Born 2006 · He/Him
    </p>
    <hr class="border-rule mt-6" />
  </header>

  <!-- Fact box (float right on desktop, inline on mobile) -->
  <aside class="float-none w-full md:float-right md:w-[30%] md:ml-8 md:mb-4 mb-6 border border-rule p-5 bg-[#F2EFE8] dark:bg-night-paper">
    <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] tracking-widest uppercase text-accent mb-4">At a Glance</p>

    <dl class="space-y-3 font-mono text-[0.7rem]">
      <div>
        <dt class="tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted">Current Role</dt>
        <dd class="text-ink mt-0.5">SF Youth Poet Laureate 2024</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted">Research</dt>
        <dd class="text-ink mt-0.5">UCSF Neuroscape Lab</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted">Engineering</dt>
        <dd class="text-ink mt-0.5">Cardinal Robotics — Tech Lead</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted">Founded</dt>
        <dd class="text-ink mt-0.5">PlayKits.org (2022)</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted">Education</dt>
        <dd class="text-ink mt-0.5">San Francisco, CA</dd>
      </div>
      <div>
        <dt class="tracking-wider uppercase text-ink-muted">Interests</dt>
        <dd class="text-ink mt-0.5">Cognitive neuroscience, robotics, pedagogy, urban poetry</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </aside>

  <!-- Profile essay -->
  <div class="font-serif text-body text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-5">

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — Opening paragraph: introduce Karan as a person who
      operates across disciplines that most people treat as separate — poetry, engineering,
      neuroscience, nonprofit work. Set the tone: curious, grounded, specific. Avoid generic
      "passionate about making a difference" language.]
    </p>

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — On growing up in San Francisco: the specific textures
      of the city, what it means to be a teenager here during a period of rapid transformation.
      The particular combination of access and inequality. How place shapes a person's questions.]
    </p>

    <PullQuote
      quote="I am interested in the questions that fall between disciplines — the ones that poetry can ask but engineering has to answer, or vice versa."
      attribution="Karan Gupta"
    />

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — On being a first-generation student navigating elite
      institutions: what it costs, what it offers, what you learn about yourself in the gap
      between where you came from and where you're going.]
    </p>

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — On PlayKits specifically: why children who have
      experienced trauma need play as a healing modality, what it looks like to design
      a kit that meets a child where they are emotionally, and what you've learned about
      resilience from the families and clinicians you partner with.]
    </p>

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — On the Neuroscape research: what drew you to
      cognitive neuroscience, how it connects to questions about attention and learning
      that also appear in your poetry, the particular excitement of working at the
      boundary of what is known.]
    </p>

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — On poetry as practice: not as hobby or sideline
      but as the primary technology for processing experience. What writing teaches you
      about thinking. The relationship between revision in poetry and debugging in code.]
    </p>

    <p>
      [PROFILE PARAGRAPH PLACEHOLDER — Closing paragraph: what you're working toward.
      Not a five-year plan but a direction, a set of questions you want to spend your life
      getting better at asking.]
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="clear-both"></div>

  <RuleHeading title="Recognition" />

  <ul class="font-serif text-body text-ink-secondary space-y-3 list-none">
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-wider uppercase text-accent mt-1.5 shrink-0">2024</span>
      <span>San Francisco Youth Poet Laureate, appointed by Mayor Daniel Lurie</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-wider uppercase text-accent mt-1.5 shrink-0">2024</span>
      <span>Featured on KQED and FOX News California as SF Youth Poet Laureate</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-wider uppercase text-accent mt-1.5 shrink-0">2024</span>
      <span>Performed at Super Bowl press conference</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-wider uppercase text-accent mt-1.5 shrink-0">2024</span>
      <span>Cardinal Robotics Tech Lead — deployed at Apple, Sutter Health, Cadence Design Systems, and Whole Foods</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-wider uppercase text-accent mt-1.5 shrink-0">2023</span>
      <span>UCSF Neuroscape Undergraduate Research Fellowship</span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span class="font-mono text-[0.65rem] tracking-wider uppercase text-accent mt-1.5 shrink-0">2022</span>
      <span>PlayKits.org — play-based therapy kits for trauma-affected children; 500+ served</span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <RuleHeading title="Contact" />

  <p class="font-serif text-body text-ink-secondary mb-4">
    For press inquiries, collaboration proposals, speaking invitations, or workshop requests:
  </p>
  <a
    href="/contact"
    class="font-mono text-[0.7rem] tracking-widest uppercase text-accent hover:text-accent-hover border-b border-accent pb-0.5 transition-colors duration-150"
  >
    Open the Contact Form →
  </a>

</ArticleLayout>
